  "body": "### The Issue\r\nCurrently the only way to add a local account is to use `Accounts.add` from within the console. Then `Accounts.load` and `Accounts.save` are available for persisting these accounts between sessions. Given the importance of local accounts when accessing non-local networks via Infura, this functionality should be much simpler to access.\r\n\r\n### Proposed Fix\r\nAdd a new section to the cli `brownie accounts` with the following functionality:\r\n\r\n- [ ] list currently available local accounts (by address and alias)\r\n- add new accounts\r\n  - [ ] by importing a keystore file\r\n  - [ ] by entering a private key\r\n  - [ ] with brownie generating a private key\r\n- [ ] delete existing accounts\r\n- [ ] change account alias / password",
